File: Eskom implements Stage 2 load-shedding from 2pm until 10pm on Wednesday. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom says South Africa will move from stage 1 to stage 2 load-shedding at 2pm on Wednesday. According to the power utility, demand has significantly increased due to cold weather conditions. Stage 2 is to continue until 10pm. Rolling blackouts returned on Friday with Eskom struggling with capacity. Power Alert 1 - 15 July 2020 (3)k by eNCA.com on Scribd 